# TODO: name these conventions (e.g. "Test conventions")

These instructions apply automatically whenever a file matching the `applyTo`
glob above is in context. Unlike an agent or a prompt, you never invoke this —
Copilot injects it for you. This mirrors the worked examples in
`.github/instructions/`.

When working on these files in this project:

- <rule 1, a concrete, checkable convention, e.g. "Use `pytest`, not `unittest`">
- <rule 2, prefer specifics over vibes, e.g. "Compare floats with `pytest.approx`">
- <rule 3, often a "do NOT", e.g. "Do not emit `pip install` cells">
- <rule 4>
- <rule 5>
